<br>
I've been playing since the server came up and been having all sorts of fun. Yes, things were chaotic and cramped when 90% of the players were 1-15th, but that's already starting to change.<br>
<br>
I play with a few friends and haven't interacted in any way with any of these guilds. I haven't had or caused any problems. Just been having fun.<br>
<br>
/soapbox on<br>
But, I just wanted to take this opportunity to go on MY soapbox a bit. I've seen people complain about &quot;intentional training&quot; a lot. My favorite line was when someone complained vigorously about being &quot;trained off the bridge&quot; in EK.<br>
<br>
Let me give you some basic advice. If you sit on railroad tracks, you're gonna get hit by a train. Trying to sit at a zone to hunt is ridiculous. You may as well sit in front of a fire escape and yell &quot;fire&quot;. If I am ever in trouble and need to zone out to save my life, I run for the zone (duh). I do my best to warn people in the area, but I refuse to stand there and die because someone has decided to sit in front of the emergency exit! Get real! You can complain until you're blue in the face that you were &quot;intentionally trained&quot;, but it means nothing if you were at a zone, because the trainer can just say he was running from the monsters. Usually, that's exactly what's happening and no malice is intended.<br>
<br>
The other funny thing being complained about is &quot;ninja looting&quot;. People are complaining that they have to stop in the middle of fights to loot corpses to prevent others from looting them. First off, &quot;ninja looting&quot; is a term that came from days before everyone in your group got a message when a group member looted an item. Sometimes group members would grab an item from a group-killed monster and then pretend they hadn't. That's WHY they put in the loot messages. Ninja looting no longer exists. Sure, a group member can still snag a rare item, disband and take off, but there's nothing &quot;ninja&quot; about it because it's quite obvious what happened thanks to the loot messages.<br>
<br>
If you (or your team) killed a monster, they have a &quot;significant&quot; amount of time to loot the monster before it becomes publicly available to any passing stranger. If you are really SO busy that you can't get to your looting in that time, you'd better get organized or loot mid-fight. It's just common sense. The person I refer to was complaining about the Warrens. Well, there are dead kobolds all over the place in there sometimes. Perhaps the killers died or trained out, people WILL stop to see if they can loot unlooted corpses. This is completely normal and happens everywhere on every server, so it makes no sense to complain about it.<br>
/soapbox off<br>
<br>
Anyway, I am happy to see the server population plummet over the last couple weeks and have had a lot of great interaction with most of the people I've met.<br>
<br>
