<br>
It has become common practice that in normal zones with special encounter mobs (Lucan comes to mind) on a normal server with no drop loot, some GM's and Guides will aid when a MORON loots an item not meant for them. But you are just as likely to be told... &quot;Sorry we cant help&quot; in that situation.<br>
<br>
Certain zones that require heavy team work and lots of time to kill mobs that fell with in the nodrop loot situation were treated different after &quot;ninja&quot; looting started to become an issue. But even that is subject to the whim of the responding GM/Guide.<br>
<br>
Dont confuse what SHOULD happen with what is or is not a RULE under the protection of Verant. There are still incidents on the main servers that are defined as &quot;ninja&quot; looting where in the GM will track down what happened BUT wont do anymore than confirm that the item was taken by soandso. At that point it becomes a matter of reputation and how the server population feels about the incident when informed. At the same time there are occasions reported where the GM removed the item and returned it to whom ever somehow convinced or proved it should have been theirs. Depends on the Whim of the responding GM. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=95.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=95.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=95.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.threadControl?topicID=95.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=95.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=95.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><tabl